  "title": "Quantity Surveyor (Senior)",
  "description": "<ul>\n  <li>Proficient in reading and interpreting drawings, and performing accurate measurements.</li>\n  <li>Skilled in preparing Bills of Quantities for various project scopes.</li>\n  <li>Well-versed in reviewing and understanding tender documents, contracts, specifications, and contractual terms.</li>\n  <li>Capable of analyzing quotations, prices, and rates, including building up rates and performing detailed pricing.</li>\n  <li>Experienced in contract administration, including valuation of progress payments and variation claims in accordance with contract requirements.</li>\n  <li>Competent in executing all tendering activities required for the procurement of new projects.</li>\n  <li>Able to carry out additional tasks related to the operations of the holding company.</li>\n  <li>Demonstrates the ability to work both independently and collaboratively within a team.</li>\n  <li>Willingly participates in ancillary company activities such as charity and corporate social responsibility events.</li>\n  <li>Consistently meets obligations within set deadlines and operational constraints.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Requirements</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Bachelor's Degree in Quantity Surveying</li>\n</ul>\n<p>We regret only shortlisted candidates will be contacted. All applications will be handled confidentially. By submitting your application, you agree to the collection, use, retention, and disclosure of your personal information to prospective employers.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>EA License No: 20C0270</p>\n<p>EA Personnel No: R22110981</p>\n<p>EA Personnel Name: Law Mei Fong</p>",
